            <pb id="p03-18" n="18"/>
            <div1 id="BQ-03-1-0006">
                <head>
                    <title type="section">
                        <hi rend="i">CORRECTION</hi>
                    </title>
                </head>
                <p>Sir Geoffrey Keynes wishes to point out that the second edition of <hi rend="i">Blake’s
Letters</hi> contains four letters not included in the first edition, and not one, as was stated in the Spring
<hi rend="i">Newsletter.</hi> In addition to the brief letter to Mrs. Aders, there are two complete letters to
Hayley and one to Linnell<corr type="emend">.</corr> Furthermore, the inverted commas in the poem sent to
Butts are not editorial, but form part of Blake’s original letter.</p>
            </div1>
        </body>
